The paper is about a graph-based semi-supervised learning approach for interactive image segmentation tasks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The approach involves optimizing feature weights to build a proper network for the segmentation task, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach also involves evaluating candidate networks, which involves graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the approach is applied to real-world images, which involves multimedia (cs.MM).
